questions.question:
What is the output of the following code?

int x = 10;
while (x < 5) {
    System.out.println(x);
    x++;
}
System.out.println("Done");

What is the output of the following code?

int x = 10;
do {
    System.out.println(x);
    x++;
} while (x < 5);
System.out.println("Done");

In the following code, what is the sentinel value?

int number = scanner.nextInt();
while (number != -1) {
    sum += number;
    number = scanner.nextInt();
}

What is the output of the following code?

int a = 5;
while (a < 5) {
    System.out.println("while: " + a);
    a++;
}
System.out.println("a = " + a);

What is the output of the following code?

int b = 5;
do {
    System.out.println("do-while: " + b);
    b++;
} while (b < 5);
System.out.println("b = " + b);

What is the value of sum after this code executes?

int sum = 0;
int i = 1;
while (i <= 5) {
    sum += i;
    i++;
}

How many times does the body of this loop execute?

int count = 0;
int value = 1000;
while (value > 0) {
    value = value / 2;
    count++;
}

What is the output of this code?

int n = 1;
do {
    System.out.print(n + " ");
    n *= 2;
} while (n <= 16);

What is the output of this code?

int i = 0;
while (i < 3) {
    i++;
    System.out.print(i + " ");
}
